reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on November 6, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Powerful handheld 5-speed TURBO fan for make-up, setting nails, traveling
reviews.reviewText: The media could not be loaded. This is the most powerful handheld fan I’ve ever seen. This turbo fan has 5 powerful speeds and comes with a charging cable & wrist strap. I’ve used it to set make up, to speed up the drying process of wet nails, and when I travel. I haven’t had to charge it yet as the battery lasts long on a single charge. This fan meets the definition of a TURBO fan. On the lower settings its quite powerful and runs fairy quietly but as you increase the speed, it does get a little louder each time but not too loud. It’s really not until you get to the last two speeds that you’ll hear a louder whirring sound (see video). The fan is sturdy even when on the highest speed. The parts are made of a very thick & durable plastic. It’s roughly an inch taller than an iPhone 13 Pro for size reference. It’s not heavy but the handle part has a little weight to it due the battery inside.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 6, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Good Quality Fan. Good for Watercolor.
reviews.reviewText: I am an intermediate level watercolor artist and I was looking for a fan to use to dry my work in between layers. This fan honestly surprised me. The reviews that I read said that it was a good fan and it was a powerful fan.They were right.This fan has five speeds, is USB-C rechargeable, and while it isn't small per-say, it's not large. It's small enough to sit in my art supply box and not take up a bunch of room.It's not "Knock a guy out with one whack" heavy, but heavy enough to feel sturdy. It's got a really good hand feel. The weight is mostly in the handle of it. I assume this is due to the battery and motor. I could hold this in my hand for a good part of the day. (I will come summer and with more watercolor paintings)The third and fourth speed drys my paper in a reasonable amount of time.WHO BOY the fifth speed of it almost (almost not quite) blows my watercolor paper away if I'm not holding it. While holding it, it does dry it (obviously) faster.I can't speak on the battery life as I have not had it long.It is a surprisingly powerful fan and I will be buying a second one once pay-day hits.The ONLY cons I have to this fan:-There is only one button. You have to cycle through the 6 clicks. 1-5 speeds and 6th click turns it off.Once you get the hang of clicking it fast through the modes it isn't too bad.-The wrist strap is hard to hook though. Doable, just hard.If I have more I'll edit.Very glad I bought this instead of an artist-eccentric one as this is much more versatile.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on November 6, 2023
reviews.reviewText: If you are hot natured this is the fan for you!I purchased this on prime day. I purchased this fan after I read the reviews and read that it has five speeds vs the three speed fan I already have. The air curculates well. For a small fan I was surprised that it had the power to keep me cool. I use the fan daily, I wish it would blink when the battery is getting low instead of just shutting off. When I use the fan for a short period the battery can sometimes last two weeks. I try and charge it at the end of the week overnight so it will be charged for Monday. This was worth the money, after using this fan I won't use another fan. I also wish the charging cable was longer. Luckily I have a longer USB-c charging cord.

reviews.reviewText: I love love love this handheld fan so much! I purchased it in the matte tan colour and it is beautiful with a sleek modern bladeless design. The next best thing is that it is rechargeable with a C-type recharging cable so no waste buying batteries here. Highly recommend this one it is the best!
